    <string name="settings_strict_section">Strict mode</string>
    <string name="strict_title">Lock system Settings too</string>
    <string name="strict_body">Stops the shield from being switched off quietly — opening Android Settings will ask for a code as well. Turning strict mode on is free; turning it off needs a code.</string>
    <string name="settings_how_section">How Pact works</string>
    <string name="how_body">Pact runs entirely on this phone — no account, no server, no internet. Unlock codes are standard authenticator codes (TOTP): your sponsor\'s phone and yours compute the same 6-digit number from a shared key and the clock, so codes work even with both phones offline.\n\nThe key appeared exactly once, during setup, and only your sponsor has it. On this phone it\'s stored encrypted inside the Android Keystore.</string>
